<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-05-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-05-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="1615" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1615">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.77/112.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">American
                                Minister</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-05-07">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 7, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>What progress has been made in the Aguadulce railway project? See
                            Department’s No. 42. While the examination should be careful and
                            thorough, it is highly desirable that it proceed as rapidly as
                            possible.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>